            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Note that when &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt; is invoked with multiple file names, it prefixes the found lines with the name of the file it was found in (unless you turn that behaviour off).  It can also report the line numbers in the individual files.  If only use &lt;code&gt;cat&lt;/code&gt; to feed &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt;, you lose the file names, and the line numbers are continuous over all files, not per file.  Thus there are reasons for having &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt; handle multiple files itself that &lt;code&gt;cat&lt;/code&gt; cannot handle.  The single file and zero file cases are simply special cases of the general multi-file use of &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/15168/jonathan-leffler&quot; title=&quot;700,796 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Jonathan Leffler&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
