            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;placing the &quot;&amp;lt; somefile&quot; before &quot;command&quot; technically gives you left to right, but it makes for ambiguous reading because there is no syntactic demarcation: &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt; cat grep dog&lt;/code&gt; is a contrived example to show that you can&apos;t easily tell between the input file, the command that receives the input, and the arguments to the command.&lt;/span&gt;

