                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;In this invocation &lt;code&gt;cat file | wc -c&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;wc&lt;/code&gt; needs to read stdin until EOF, counting bytes. But in this, &lt;code&gt;wc -c &amp;lt; file&lt;/code&gt;, it just stats stdin, finds out it&apos;s a regular file and print st_size instead of reading any input. For a large file the difference in performance would be clearly visible.&lt;/span&gt;

