                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Your own blog shows a 50% slowdown for high-throughput, and you aren&apos;t even looking at the impact on total throughput (if you had stuff keeping the other cores busy).  If I get around to it, I might run your tests while x264 or x265 are encoding a video using all cores, and see how much it slows down the video encoding.  &lt;code&gt;bzip2&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;gzip&lt;/code&gt; compression are both very slow compared to the amount of overhead &lt;code&gt;cat&lt;/code&gt; adds to that alone (with the machine otherwise idle).  It&apos;s hard to read your tables (line wrap in the middle of a number?). &lt;code&gt;sys&lt;/code&gt; time increases a lot, but still small vs. user or real?&lt;/span&gt;

